items.name: PPK (GFL)
items.description:
• Install this extension for webui to access LoHA models: https://github.com/KohakuBlueleaf/a1111-sd-webui-locon.

Features PPK (Polizeipistole Kriminalmodell) from Girls' Frontline in her original costume & Mach Tempest racing costume, trained on animefull-latest with the awkward combination of LoHA+Lion optimizer.

Neither its output quality nor cross-checkpoint compatibility appeared potent enough to justify for all the trouble involved, as such for future models I'll probably revert to the tried ACM+LoHA+DAdapt formula; any help or suggestions on this topic are still welcomed though.

Works acceptably up to full weight (1.0) on test runs, yet due to the small training data being of subpar quality and split between 2 costumes, it could appear to be lossy at full weight on some checkpoints (CetusMix specifically; as of MeinaMix my LoRA never seemed to work either, reasons unknown).

Prompts

(Non-exhaustive list of details, skewer out what you deem unnecessary)

  • Basic character features: ppkgfl, small breasts, very long hair,

  • Default costume: frilled hairband, gothic lolita, lolita fashion, short frilled dress, puffy short sleeves, black gloves, single thighhigh, kneehighs, mismatched legwear, asymmetrical legwear, uneven legwear, legwear garter, black platform footwear,

  • Racing costume: visor cap, white belt, leotard, see-through, skin tight, bare shoulders, elbow gloves, fingerless gloves, white thighhighs, thigh boots,

  • rough digimind upgrade MOD3 costume (very few training done & high chance of element leakage from the racing outfit observed): black dress, bare shoulders, detached sleeves, choker, black gloves, black pantyhose, thigh boots, high heel boots,

    • Putting "white headwear, frilled hairband, visor cap, elbow gloves, white thighhighs" to the negative prompt field helps with her MOD3 costume by a margin.

items.name: .hack//SIGN Mimiru
items.description:
Trained on 77 images of Mimiru from .hack//SIGN, extracted the show.

Trigger is dothack_mimiru. To get her armor usually "bikini armor" works.

Some of the training data is sourced from dungeon areas of the show. As a result, sometimes the armor comes out very purple or black. I'm working on a way to try and prevent this and may have to retrain the model in the future without these images. For now, I recommend trying to regenerate whenever this happens.

Certain characteristics, such as her leg armor, will come out inconsistent. There are not many full body shots in the anime. Furthermore, the show itself is sometimes inconsistent on certain things, such as the red jewel on her skirt.

This is my first ever public release of a LoRA. I typically make these for myself, but wanted to try sharing one. If you like my work and would like me to work on releasing additional models, you can let me know here or over at my Patreon https://www.patreon.com/edit/about

items.name: Hinata Hyuga Character LoRA
items.description:
Hinata Hyuga Character LoRA

If you enjoy my models and want to support me you could buy me a coffee!

This LoRA mimics the character Hinata Hyuga from Naruto.

The example images were created with NeverEndingDream on varying weight but feel free to experiment on your own. I tried briefly to mix it with a couple of different embeddings and it gave back decent results but you might find a better way to mix them (changing different weights etc.).

I did mess up a little bit in the creation of the LoRA so it sometimes gives you some text in the corner in a watermark-type style. Also you could need to add "collar, choker, konohagakure symbol" to the negative prompts if you don't want the headband.

To change the weight just change the '1' in this prompt: <lora:hinata-Hyuga-LoRA:1>.

I'd love to see the art you guys make with it so feel free to add them in comments.

How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight (by default it's :1 which is usually too high)

Recommendations of use:
---------------------------------------------
Enable Quantization in K samplers.

Avoid or Do not add ' Photorealistic ', ' 3d ' or ' realistic ' in the prompt. Those tend to make weird generations in V1.

Negatives: ' (worst quality, low quality:1.4), monochrome, zombie, '

The best samplers in most of the generations is Euler a - 25 steps OR Euler - 50 steps. ( Clip skip 2. )

Resolution: 512x768 , 512x1024 is unstable and others resolutions may work but they're not tested.

Upscaler in most of the scenarios is R-ESRGAN 4x or +Anime6B, with 15 steps at 0.1 up to 0.3 denoising.

sprinkledpastels style - more realistic character proportion compared to playfulwhimsy (like comics or graphic novels), lots of random colorful elements scattered around, complex compositions

items.name: Cheer Uniform
items.description:
New "modern" version

The original version is still good, but it based on the "classic" (think Night of Comet) cheerleader look that hasn't actually been used by cheerleaders for decades.

This new version is trained on the modern look. Choose whichever look you prefer. Strength of 1 gives a pretty standard result. Lower values give more creativity, usually reveal some midriff.

Keywords:

Modern version: moderncheerunifrom

Classic ("v1.0") version: cheeruniform

Info from Original ("1") version (still good!):

Fairly self-explanatory model. It is trained on over 400 adult cheerleader costumes (many of them sort of the "slutty Halloween" type). Using the phrase "cheerleader uniform" (or outfit or whatever) can also cause models to make the person wearing the uniform look like a stereotypical cheerleader, which may not be what you want. These were therefore trained with the keyword "cheeruniform" to focus entirely on the uniform and not the person wearing it. You must include the word cheeruniform (no spaces) for it to work.

The model is very strong. I included two images that show the same seed/prompt with various weightings. You can also use the LoRA to create cheeruniform-like clothing, such as the steampunk outfit I included.

I include things like ((words)) ((text)) ((logo)) in the negative prompt, but the awful lettering still creeps into a lot of the results.

"I feel a little under-dressed, but at least I'm not dressed like a slutty cheerleader, right?"

items.name: No more color contamination - Read Description
items.description:
READ THE DESCRIPTION


Do not download LoRa (NOT NECESSARY)


This is a simple and powerful tutorial, I uploaded a LORA file because it was mandatory to upload something, it has nothing to do with the tutorial. Tribute and credit to hnmr293.


Step 1: Install this extension

Step 2: Restart Stable Diffusion (close and open)


Step 3: Enable Cutoff (in txt2img under controlnet or additional network)

Step 4: Put in positive prompt: a cute girl, white shirt with green tie, red shoes, blue hair, yellow eyes, pink skirt


Step 5: Put in negative prompt: (low quality, worst quality:1.4), nsfw


Step 6: Put in Target tokens (Cutoff): white, green, red, blue, yellow, pink

Step 7: Put 2 of weight. Leave everything else as the image.

Tips:

0# Give priority to colors, first them and then everything else, 1girl, masterpiece... but without going overboard, remember tip #3

1# The last Token of Target Token must have "," like this: white, green, red, blue, yellow, pink, 👈 ATTENTION: For some people it works to put a comma at the end of the token, for others this gives an error. If you see that it has an error, delete it.

2# The color should always come before the clothes. Not knowing much English happened to me that I put the colors after the clothes or the eyes and the changes were not applied to me.

3# Do not go over 75 token. It is a problem if they go to 150 or 200 tokens.

4# If you don't put any negative prompt, it can give an error.

5# Do not use token weights below 1 eg: (red hoddie:0.5)

20 images were always worked on and in most of the tests it was 100%. If they put, for example, green pants, some jean pants (blue) can appear, also with the skirts a black skirt can appear. These "mistakes" can happen.

That's why I put 95% in the title because 1 or 2 images out of 20 images may appear with this error.

items.name: 【Character】Hamel (Path to Nowhere)
items.description:
Introduction

A LoRA model of Hamel from Path to Nowhere, including 2 outfits, default and christmas outfit. The 784mb VAEs (NovelAI, Anythingv3, Orangemix, Counterfeit) are recommended. 0.6 ~ 0.8 weights are good. The preview images are generated using latest version of YesMix and EasyNegative embedding.

Usage

The universal trigger tag is 'hamel'.

  • For default outfit, the key features are 'black dress, detached sleeves, blue hair, long hair, chain, jellyfish'.

  • For christmas outfit, the key features are 'red dress, short hair, hair ornament, red bow, christmas, merry christmas'.

See the preview images for the details.

Cautions (Must Read)

  • Some preview images are generated using hires fix. Thus, the generating results will be different even though using the same prompt (and seed) contained in preview images due to 'Denoising' value and 'Hires Steps' in hires fix panel.

  • The maximum of generating resolution should not exceed 1024, otherwise extra/deformed head/limbs will be waiting for you :). Try to use 'hires fix' to prevent this problem and help to generate higher-resolution images.

  • For 784mb VAEs (NovelAI, Anythingv3, Orangemix, Counterfeit) users, make sure add '--no-half-vae' in command line of webui to prevent generating black images. See voldy's log for the details of edit method. For high-performance GPU, make sure 'medvram' and 'lowvram' mode are disabled.

This model was trained on NAI anime-full-pruned and generated in AOM3. Made with the Kohya tool for AI Training. Any suggestions to improve or recommended things for the data set would be appreciated.
*When using this use the words 'solid eyes' and 'colored sclera' together to increase chances for the full effect.

modelVersions.name: v7.0
modelVersions.description: If using this at 0.6 use solid eyes and colored sclera together. This version was made for easier compatibility with more epochs. If using this at a solid 1 only solid eyes is necessary. This version has added pictures to the dataset and lower quality ones removed.

modelVersions.name: Solid Eyes V6
modelVersions.description:
After several attempts to increase consistency and control of the eyes why lowering step count to make a less burned effect I got this version. This version has expanded training data with distributed weights based on resolution as well as some personally cropped close ups of faces to give as accurate training data as possible why decreasing step count. If using the prompt 'solid eyes' alone the eye will still have white sclera but with no pupil adding the term 'colored sclera' applies the same color to the whole eye so no need to specify sclera color.

I couldn't find any LoRA models that had the specific makeup look I was looking for, in particular "Bimbo makeup", so I've decided to train my own.

I haven't done extensive testing on it, but from my preliminary testing it seems to have gotten the idea.

I'm brand new to training LoRA models, and this was the first to actually come out looking alright. My apologies if my inexperience shines through and makes this an actually terrible model. I had a specific use case for this going in, and I'm mainly sharing as a bit of a formality for people that are also looking for something similar.

By all means let me know what issues you have with it, but I probably won't be able to fix them unless you yourself have a suggestion on how to do it. I don't really know what I'm doing ¯\_(ツ)_/¯ and I'm kinda just throwing things at the wall and seeing what works.

items.name: Kavka's Dracowolf Lora (V5)
items.description:
I had gotten a little bored one day, and decided to figure out how to create a lora of the species my OC is based on, the dracowolves. Hybridized creatures of wolves and dragons, my own little take on the creatures.

I got this sucker baked well enough that you should be able to use it at full strength, and the main trigger word is "dracowolf", also at full strength. You don't need to include horns, it'll certainly give you that, though it will also try to stick to just the dual horns on the head. It'll certainly want to stick to the traditional colours of my character, but I've found some success in changing those details. Even the variations are still considered a dracowolf to me.

This was trained on my personal checkpoint, KavkaMix

Works great with other Loras. I personally like using this for a nice Final Fantasy feel in conjunction with others such as this for some high-contrast. I'll include examples using other Loras to show the drastic differences.

When doing headshot portraits very little modification is needed. You can use all the additional suggested tags (along with the more intricate detailed prompts as shown in the example pics), but I only use things like "scaled belly, furred back" when it wants to do a scale/fur blend..which can also look nice. "Canine features" does help with the face/head.

Enjoy!

Update March 26, 2023

Trained on KavkaMixV1.2

Great results without needing other Loras, but those are always fun to play around with!

Key prompts: dracowolf, canine features, scaled forearms, scaled hands, scaled belly, scaled chest, furred legs, furred biceps

Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras

Steps: 25

CFG: 7

512x512 or 512x768

You can support by buying a coffee ☕️ here —

https://ko-fi.com/kusackavka

Be warned about the tails. Can be wonderful, can be cursed. Ye have been warned, and I shall continue to work on this along with my checkpoint. Nudity might require the assistance of other Loras. I sometimes use this.

modelVersions.name: V5
modelVersions.description: An enhanced version of the previous one.

modelVersions.name: V4-Regularization
modelVersions.description:
This one's been quite baked. Been learning regularization, and as a result had doubled the total number of steps. Seems to have turned out well. Some additional trigger words are needed for full dracowolf effects. Adjust as needed for whatever type of portrait is desired.

Trained on KavkaMixV1.2

Key prompts: dracowolf, canine features, scaled forearms, scaled hands, scaled belly, scaled chest, furred legs, furred biceps

Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras

Steps: 25

CFG: 7

512x512 or 512x768. Landscape (768x512) can work if you're patient enough.

modelVersions.name: v3
modelVersions.description:
Releasing this one earlier than intended, as the results were way better than expected.

Normally I use AdamW8bit as the optimizer when creating Loras, but this time used AdamW. I have to say that I'm very impressed, though now have to be careful using (photographic quality) as that seems to turn the pics black and white or even grayscale.

The following prompts help fleshing out the details. Adjust as according to type of picture (bust, half-length, full portrait): (scaled forearms, scaled hands:1.3), (scaled belly, scaled chest:1.3), white hands, (scale covered body), (fur covered body:1.3), white hands, (furred legs, furred biceps:1.3), (canine features:1.2), (hyper realistic scales:1.2), (hyper realistic fur:1.4), (detailed fur:1.3), (detailed scales:1.2)

Example pics will be, as before, without and then with some other Loras. Hypernetworks aren't as required, unless you're having issues getting the fur to stand out.

modelVersions.name: V2
modelVersions.description:
Again, shown with and without other loras. This version gives a bit more flexibility to body shape and colouring. Female dracowolves are also possible, but you might have to up the emphasis on the tags. Might also need to lower the lora to 0.8-0.9 to start bringing the variations out.

Sadly, tails are still a bit of an issue.

items.description:
A LORA of Alba B. belatedly uploaded, by request. Trained using the Kohya_ss gui on about 30 images on vanilla SD 1.5. This was my 4th attempt and it works fairly well with various realistic and Anime based models. Can be a bit frustrating at high prompt weights and I would suggest Clip skip 2 and using DPM++ 2M Karras as the sampler. Prompt info should be attached to the images.

There are no tags just use "<lora:Albapt2:1>" in your prompt somewhere. Prompt strength should be anywhere from 0.5 to 0.7 though some models will work with the full weight. It is a bit over-trained I think, though it is flexible enough to change hair, eye, and skin color and to add expressions.

items.name: Reverse Three iCo
items.description:
Hello! I am not a model maker, I am not the original creator of the models in this merge. I am only someone who weighted merged these two models together and sharing it.
This Model is NSFW biased.

This model is a merge of the "three" model by discord member Dr. Derp, and the iCoMixV2 found here:
https://civitai.com/models/16164/icomix

It was merge block weighted with RSmoothStep2, with "three" as Model A, hence the name Revese-Three-iCo.

Dr. Derp recommends aspect ratio 512x704 or similar. As far as I know, no VAE is needed, HOWEVER, the use of SD-VAE, or Anything-VAE is likely good due to iCo using Anything and SD-VAE being generally good.

SD VAE:
https://huggingface.co/stabilityai/sd-vae-ft-mse
Anything VAE:
https://huggingface.co/andite/anything-v4.0/blob/main/anything-v4.0.vae.pt
The sample images we generated using the Bad Prompt V2 embedding at a .50 weight (ex: bad_prompt_v2:0.50)
found here:
https://huggingface.co/datasets/Nerfgun3/bad_prompt/blob/main/bad_prompt_version2.pt

And ControlNet found in WebUI Extensions, I can't speak to other methods.

Here's my DeviantArt page where I post SFW and NSFW content:
https://www.deviantart.com/adellanuki

items.description:
This lora was based on the model anythingv4.5 and trained by picture of the sajou manaka in Fate/Prototype, there are many problems in the first attempt, which may be improve after being skilled. It is recommended that the weight be around 0.8 with tag:sajoumanaka,1 girl at the front of the prompt may be better at least that's what I tested.

2023.4.25

Update the new version sajoumanakaV2.0

2023.5.22

Update the new version sajoumanakaV3.0

modelVersions.name: v2.0
modelVersions.description: This time, I tried using the SD1.5 model for training, and the stability of the produced images and characters was significantly improved, but some details were not well represented. Even if images with rei ju are added to the training set, they cannot be restored. Looking for a solution.

modelVersions.name: v1.0
modelVersions.description: This version is relatively stable among the models with the lowest loss value (loss=0.116) selected from 6 training sessions and 10 models each time. Try to use it in anythingv3 with good result, and try to use it in counterfeit-v2.5, but the stability is a little poor.
